natspec.details: NFT contract for Track Pack purchasing and burning

createToken(string).details: Only owner function to mint a new NFT.

params.newTokenURI: the token URI on IPFS for the NFT metadata

returns._0: the ID of the newly minted NFT

getRequestStatus(uint256).details: Function for getting the status of a random number request.

params._requestId: the ID of the random number request - created in the openTrackPackNFT function

returns.fulfilled: whether or not the random numbers have been given for the supplied request ID
returns.randomWords: the list of random numbers for the request - empty list if not fulfilled
returns.tokenIds: the list of song token IDs that were minted in the openTrackPackNFT function when the random numbers were requested

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getUserTokenIDs(address).details: Function to get all token IDs for tokens that a given user owns.

params.userAddress: the user's address to get token IDs of

returns._0: list of token IDs for a user's NFTs

getUserTokenURIs(address).details: Function to get all token URIs for tokens that a given user owns.

params.userAddress: the user's address to get token URIs of

returns._0: list of token URIs for a user's NFTs

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

mintTrackPackNFT(uint256).details: Allows someone to mint a Track Pack NFT by paying USDC

params.nftCount: the number of NFTs to mint

returns._0: newItemIds the ID(s) of the newly minted Track Pack NFT(s)

openTrackPackNFT(uint256).details: Function to open a Track Pack NFT - also mints the song NFTs and requests random numbers from Chainlink VRF to start the song assignment.

params.tokenId: the ID of the token to burn for the track pack opening

returns._0: requestId the request ID for the random number generation

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).details: Setter function for the token URI of an NFT.

params.newTokenURI: the token URI to update the NFT with
params.tokenId: the ID of the NFT to update the token URI of

updateCallbackGasLimit(uint32).details: Only owner function to update the callbackGasLimit value for VRF.

updateCoordinator(address).details: Only owner function to update the VRF coordinator interface.

params.newCoordinator: the new VRF coordinator interface reference

updateKeyHash(bytes32).details: Only owner function to update the keyhash for VRF.

updateMaxNFTs(uint256).details: updates the maximum number of Track Pack NFTs that can be minted for the drop this contract represents.

params.newMaxNFTs: the new maximum number of NFTs that can be minted in this contract

updateNFTPriceInUSDC(uint256).details: updates the price of each NFT.

params.newNFTPriceInUSDC: the price of each NFT in USDC

updateNumSongsPerTrackPack(uint256).details: Only owner function to update the number of songs per Track Pack.

params.newNumSongsPerTrackPack: the new number of songs per Track Pack

updateRequestConfirmations(uint16).details: Only owner function to update the requestConfirmations value for VRF.

updateSongNFT(address).details: Only owner function to update the reference to the song NFT contract.

params.newSongNFTContractAddress: the address of the new song NFT contract

updateSubscriptionId(uint64).details: Only owner function to update the Chainlink VRF subscription ID.

params.newSubscriptionId: the new Chainlink VRF subscription ID

updateTrackPackTokenURI(string).details: updates the Track Pack NFT token URI

params.newTrackPackTokenURI: the new token URI for the Track Pack NFTs

withdrawTrackPackFunds().details: Only owner function to withdraw the USDC that is paid to this contract for the Track Pack NFTs.
